## 📧 Email and Productivity

### Microsoft 365 Business Basic (Recommended)
- **Cost:** £4.60/user/month (often £5.60 with VAT)
- **Includes:** Email, OneDrive (1TB), Teams, web Office apps
- **Why:** Most UK businesses use it, good value, integrates with everything
- **Best for:** Most trades businesses
- **NorthWest Heating uses:** Microsoft 365 Business Basic

### Google Workspace
- **Cost:** £4.14/user/month (Business Starter)
- **Why:** Good if you prefer Google tools
- **Best for:** Businesses already using Gmail
- **Note:** Either Microsoft or Google is fine, pick one and stick with it

**Don't use:** Free personal Gmail/Outlook for business (unprofessional, no support)

---

## 💼 Accounting Software

### Xero (Recommended)
- **Cost:** £12/month (Early), £30/month (Growing)
- **Why:** Popular in UK, cloud-based, integrates with banks
- **Best for:** Most small trades businesses
- **NorthWest Heating uses:** Xero

### QuickBooks Online
- **Cost:** £10/month (Simple Start), £20/month (Essentials)
- **Why:** Also popular, good features
- **Best for:** Alternative to Xero if you prefer it

### Sage
- **Cost:** £10/month (Accounting Start)
- **Why:** Traditional choice, widely used
- **Best for:** Those already familiar with Sage

**All three are good. Pick based on what your accountant recommends.**

